<DOCNO> APW20000701.0035 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-01 07:40 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Magic Johnson Theaters opens, giving Harlem its first multiplex  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Former Los Angeles Lakers star Magic Johnson was
in Harlem on Friday to open the area's first multiplex movie
theater.
</P>
<P>
   ''This theater was long overdue,'' said Johnson at the grand
opening. ''The community is ready for this theater and I know they
appreciate it.''
</P>
<P>
   The new nine-screen theater is the most recent part of the
revitalization of 125th Street, the broad street that serves as
Harlem's main thoroughfare. The Magic Johnson Theaters is part of
the new $66 million Harlem U.S.A. shopping and entertainment
complex at 125th and Frederick Douglass Boulevard.
</P>
<P>
   Other stores recently opened on 125th include HMV Records,
Starbucks, Krispy Kreme, Old Navy, the Disney Store and Modell's
Sporting Goods.
</P>
<P>
   The Johnson theater features first-run movies and seating for
2,700. The auditoriums are furnished with plush, oversized rocking
chair seats, state-of-the-art projection and digital sound.
</P>
<P>
   Since 1995, Johnson has partnered with Loews Cineplex
Entertainment to open movie theaters in urban neighborhoods in Los
Angeles, Houston, Atlanta and Cleveland.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-07-01-00 0740 </TRAILER>
