<HEADLINE> Baby sitter accused of murdering her charge  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - A Brooklyn baby sitter is charged with murdering
a 1-year-old girl in her care.
</P>
<P>
   Nebelyn Heyeras died at 12:45 p.m. Friday, about an hour after
paramedics were called to the apartment where Marlene Tejada, 16,
was baby-sitting her, said Officer George Jensen, a police
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   He said Nebelyn stopped breathing while she was eating. Police
said Tejada gave her an unidentified liquid.
</P>
<P>
   After the child died, Tejada was arrested and charged with
second-degree murder.
</P>
</TEXT>
