<HEADLINE> Terrace Collapses in Ohio  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIDDLE BASS, Ohio (AP) -- A terrace at an island winery in Lake
Erie collapsed Saturday afternoon, injuring at least 80 people
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   The terrace collapsed at the Lonz Winery on an island about 5
miles off the mainland.
</P>
<P>
   A dispatcher at the police department in nearby Port Clinton
said the collapse occurred about 5 p.m. He said about 60
firefighters and emergency medical personnel were on their way to
the island.
</P>
<P>
   Middle Bass is about 50 miles east of Toledo.
</P>
