<HEADLINE> Tulu Wins 10,000 Meters Race  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BRUNSWICK, Maine (AP) -- Ethiopia's Derartu Tulu, the 1992
Olympic champion in the women's 10,000 meters, outkicked Japan's
Yuko Kawakami on Saturday to win the event in the New Balance Maine
Distance Festival.
</P>
<P>
   Tulu finished in 31 minutes, 8 seconds, a second ahead of
Kawakami, who set a Japanese record.
</P>
<P>
   Adriana Fernandez of Mexico, the 1999 New York Marathon winner,
was third in 31:10, also a national best.
</P>
<P>
   Melody Fairchild was the fastest U.S. finisher at 33:34, good
for eighth place.
</P>
<P>
   Tulu and Fernandez already have qualified to run in the Olympic
marathon. By finishing under 32:30 in the 10,000, they will be able
to choose between the two events.
</P>
</TEXT>
