<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Amherst's Falgiano named Miss New York  </HEADLINE>
AP Photos
<TEXT>
<P>
   WATERTOWN, N.Y. (AP) - Kelly Falgiano of Amherst was named Miss
New York Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Falgiano, 21, will represent the state in October at the Miss
America pageant in Atlantic City. The college student hopes to
become a nurse practitioner specializing in pediatrics.
</P>
<P>
   Her platform issue was educating children on the importance of
nutrition and physical fitness.
</P>
<P>
   First runner up was Brandi Martin, 19, who was Miss Niagara
County. Martin hopes to be a defense attorney.
</P>
<P>
   Second runner up was Miss Buffalo, Krista Robusto, 18, who
aspires to be an opera singer.
</P>
<P>
   Third runner up was Miss Heart of New York, Detra McTier, 23.
She is seeking a master's degree in business and advertising and
hopes to run her own charm and etiquette school.
</P>
<P>
   Fourth runner was Miss Staten Island, 23-year-old Jennifer
Vernazza.
</P>
<P>
   Over the three-day pageant, 28 young women from around the state
vied for the title, competing in such areas as talent, swimsuit,
evening wear and an interview.
</P>
<P>
   Falgiano takes the crown from 1999's winner, Brandi Burkhardt.
</P>
</TEXT>
